('Revitalization Rye', 4698, 11, 119, 6.500000, 'This IPA is brewed with 35% rye malt. The crisp malt character is layered with Warrior hops. Dry-hopped with Warrior and Simcoe.', 'The Alchemist', 'United States'),
('Shut The Hell Up', 4699, 1, 10, 3.300000, 'An American mild ale brewed with Horizon hops. The crisp, bitter finish is helpd up by a balanced malt body.', 'The Alchemist', 'United States'),
('St. Bernardus Witbier', 4700, 5, 67, 5.500000, 'This traditional Witbier (Wheat beer) has been developed in cooperation with Master Brewer Pierre Celis, the Godfather of Hoegaarden and Celis White. \n\n\nThis beer as well has a second fermentation in the bottle, giving this beer its specific taste (5.5% alcohol content).', 'Brouwerij St. Bernardus', 'Belgium'),
