('NÃ¸gne Ã˜ Saison', 5053, 5, 74, 6.500000, 'One of our most refreshing brews, made for those hot summer days, but satisfying year \'round. Recommended serving temperature 8Â°C/45Â°F. Goes well with seafood, particularly oysters.', 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ - Det KompromisslÃ¸se Bryggeri A/S', 'Norway'),
('NÃ¸gne Ã˜ Amber Ale', 5054, 3, 33, 6.000000, 'A rather malty brew, which we think goes very well with cheeses - even well matured blue cheeses. You can also try our Amber paired with a grilled dish. Recommended serving temperature 10Â°C/50Â°F.', 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ - Det KompromisslÃ¸se Bryggeri A/S', 'Norway'),
('NÃ¸gne Ã˜ Imperial Brown Ale', 5055, 3, 38, 7.500000, 'There is a long story to this malty ale.  It was first brewed in the spring 2006 in NÃ¸rrebro Bryghus in Copenhagen, Denmark, as a joint brew between NÃ¸gne Ã˜ and NÃ¸rrebro.  NÃ¸rrebro calls their version â€œDouble Knot Brownâ€.  It is the perfect thing to drink with almost any cheese.', 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ - Det KompromisslÃ¸se Bryggeri A/S', 'Norway'),
('NÃ¸gne Ã˜ India Pale Ale', 5056, 3, 31, 6.500000, 'A rich, malty, and very bitter ale. Cascade hops provide a long, fruity, and spicy after-taste.  Recommended serving temperature 10Â°C/50Â°F.  Ideal with barbequed or smoked meat dishes.', 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ - Det KompromisslÃ¸se Bryggeri A/S', 'Norway'),
('NÃ¸gne Ã˜ #100', 5057, 3, 35, 10.000000, 'Our 100th batch, brewed for the enjoyment of the brewers, but popular demand forced us to release it commercially.  This malty, yet light bodied ale has a massive hop bitterness.  Most enjoyable in a comfortable chair in front of a roaring fire.', 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ - Det KompromisslÃ¸se Bryggeri A/S', 'Norway'),
('Krampus Imperial Helles Lager', 5058, -1, -1, 9.000000, 'St. Nicholas, aka Santa Claus, is a magical figure, the bringer of gifts and an icon of holiday spirit. Forgotten by most is his evil side kick and enforcer of â€˜the listâ€™. European tradition says while St. Nick is busy delivering presents to good little boys and girls, Krampus hands out punishments to the bad. A fanged, goat-horned bully, the Christmas Devil uses sticks and chains to beat the naughty children. Dark malts and aromatic hops create the diabolical spirit of this brew. It is finished with lager yeast and aged cold for no less than 30 days. This Imperial Helles Lager will warm even the darkest hearts. \n\n\nThis season, replace the cookies with a bottle of Krampus. If he happens to pay a visit, toast to him with this devilish brew. Merry Kramp-mas to all, and to all a good pint!\n\n9.0% abv. â€¢ 20Âº plato â€¢ Imperial Helles Lager â€¢ 22 oz / 1/6 keg', 'Southern Tier Brewing Co', 'United States'),
('Slab Cabin IPA', 5059, 3, 31, 5.000000, 'A classic American IPA with lots of floral punch and assertive hop presence. Hopped with Nugget, Palisade and Amarillo colored to a reddish hue thanks to Munich and Aromatic malts', 'Otto\'s Pub and Brewery', 'United States'),
('Warsteiner Premium Oktoberfest', 5060, 7, 84, 5.900000, '', 'Warsteiner Brauerei', 'Germany'),
